questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue where a microservice's transaction rolls back unexpectedly. An order-processing service saves an order and calls an external billing service. If the billing service throws a `BillingException` (an unchecked exception), the application catches it and attempts to save an audit log of the failure using a method annotated with `@Transactional(propagation = Propagation.REQUIRES_NEW)` inside the same service class. However, the audit log is never written to the database, and the entire transaction is rolled back.

java
@Service
public class OrderService {
    @Autowired
    private OrderRepository repository;

    @Transactional
    public void process(Order order) {
        try {
            chargeBilling(order);
        } catch (BillingException ex) {
            logFailure(order, ex.getMessage());
            throw ex;
        }
    }

    @Transactional(propagation = Propagation.REQUIRES_NEW)
    public void logFailure(Order order, String reason) {
        repository.saveLog(order.getId(), "FAILED", reason);
    }
}
